# Pipeline Filter Rules

## Rule 1 — Candidate Status Labels Always Visible

`CandidateCard.tsx` MUST show the status label for ALL three `CandidateStatus` values. Never gate it on a single state.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — always render when statusLabel is present
{statusLabel && statusConfig[statusLabel] && (
  <div style={{ color: statusConfig[statusLabel].color }}>
    {statusConfig[statusLabel].icon}
    <span>{statusConfig[statusLabel].text}</span>
  </div>
)}

// ❌ WRONG — silently drops continua + descartado
{isPorValidar && <div>Por validar</div>}
```

Status config must cover all three values:
- `continua` → CheckCircle2, `var(--color-positive-600)`, text "Continúa"
- `por_validar` → HelpCircle, `var(--color-warning-600)`, text "Por validar"
- `descartado` → XCircle, `var(--color-negative-600)`, text "Descartado"

---

## Rule 2 — Finalistas is Locked by Default

Finalistas MUST be disabled in both `ValidationPipelineFilter` and `Sidebar` unless the unlock condition is met. When locked:
- `pointer-events: none`, `opacity: 0.45`, `cursor: default`
- Count shows `–` instead of a number
- Sidebar item is greyed out and non-clickable

---

## Rule 3 — Finalistas Unlock Condition

```typescript
// Finalistas unlocks ONLY when Evaluaciones is EN PROCESO or COMPLETADO
const finalistaLocked = activeStage !== 'evaluaciones';
```

This is computed in `Candidatos.tsx` and shared via `PipelineContext`. Both `ValidationPipelineFilter` and `Sidebar` consume this context.

---

## Rule 4 — Finalistas Count Display

```tsx
// ✅ When unlocked — show 5 (or actual shortlist count)
{!finalistaLocked ? finalistCount : '–'}

// Label only shown when unlocked
{!finalistaLocked && <span>candidatos</span>}
```

Default `finalistCount` is `5`.

---

## Rule 5 — Stage Navigation Locked Progressively

Stages are navigable only when `en_proceso` or `completado`. The `getStageStatus()` function in `ValidationPipelineFilter` drives this:

```typescript
// stages BEFORE activeStage → 'completado' → clickable
// activeStage itself        → 'en_proceso'  → clickable
// stages AFTER activeStage  → 'sin_iniciar'  → locked
```

Never allow jumping ahead to a `sin_iniciar` stage. Lock via `pointer-events: none` + `opacity: 0.45`.

---

## Shared State — PipelineContext

`activeStage` is shared via `PipelineContext` (`src/context/PipelineContext.tsx`). All components that need to know the current stage or whether Finalistas is locked must consume this context — never rely on prop drilling through unrelated components.

```typescript
const { activeStage, setActiveStage } = usePipeline();
const finalistaLocked = activeStage !== 'evaluaciones';
```
